.TH "add_mem_range" 9 "add_mem_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
add_mem_range \- Updates existing memory range, if there is an overlap. Else, adds a new memory range.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" add_mem_range
.BI "(struct crash_mem **mem_ranges "  ","
.BI "u64 base "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mem_ranges" 12
Range list to add the memory range to.
.IP "base" 12
Base address of the range to add.
.IP "size" 12
Size of the memory range to add.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
(Re)allocates memory, if needed.

Returns 0 on success, negative errno on error.
